INSERT INTO `gorg_term_taxonomy` VALUES (1,1,'category','',0,0),(2,2,'nav_menu','',0,48),(3,3,'nav_menu','',0,4),(4,4,'nav_menu','',0,3),(5,5,'product_type','',0,70),(6,6,'product_type','',0,0),(7,7,'product_type','',0,0),(8,8,'product_type','',0,0),(9,9,'product_visibility','',0,0),(10,10,'product_visibility','',0,0),(11,11,'product_visibility','',0,14),(12,12,'product_visibility','',0,0),(13,13,'product_visibility','',0,0),(14,14,'product_visibility','',0,0),(15,15,'product_visibility','',0,0),(16,16,'product_visibility','',0,0),(17,17,'product_visibility','',0,0),(18,18,'product_cat','<h3>Modern Area Rug Stores Miami</h3>\r\nAt Grand Oriental Rug Gallery we carry the exquisite designer contemporary area rugs to satisfy your artistic plate. you will discover a range of contemporary area rugs in exotic patterns, Modern designs. contemporary area rugs are made in wool, silk, and combination of both. Come and choose from The Modern Tibetan contemporary area rug for your fashionable seating arrangement.',0,31),(19,19,'product_cat','<blockquote>Persian, Area, Oushak, Antique, Tabriz, Ispfhan, Naine, Kashan, Silk Qums, Ziegler, Mahal, Modern,Vegetable dyes, Kashmir silk, Bamboo silk, Agra, Mashhad, Bakhtiar, Bidjar, Farahan, Heriz, Kirman Shah, Lavar Kirman, Malayer, Mamluk, Serapi, Sultanabad, Turkish, William Morris.</blockquote>\r\nWhen talking about traditional rugs, the terms Oriental Rugs, or Persian rugs come to mind. The art, mystique, and history of Oriental Rugs make the search for them very intoxicating. History has shown that Oriental rugs stand for their captivating/marveling designs, uncompromising quality, durability, and value\r\n\r\n<b>What’s the difference?</b>\r\nOriental rug refers to a hand-woven rug made from wool, silk or cotton, woven in the Orient (a historic term for Asia), specifically Iran, China, India, Russia, Turkey, Pakistan, Tibet and Nepal. Persian rug refers to carpets exclusively woven in the Islamic Republic of Iran (before 1935, Persia).',0,4),(22,22,'product_cat','<h3>Aubusson Area Rugs. Aubusson Rugs.</h3>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">With its name originating from the French village of Aubusson near the Creuse River, these were first woven around the 16 th century and were symbolic of elegance and prestige of Imperial France. Today, the Aubusson still reflects this notion.</div>',0,0),(31,31,'pa_color','',0,14),(41,41,'pa_color','',0,4),(42,42,'pa_color','',0,7),(48,48,'pa_color','',0,11),(49,49,'pa_color','',0,3),(50,50,'pa_color','',0,6),(54,54,'product_cat','<h3>Tribal Rugs. Tribal Area Rugs.</h3>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">Nomadic woven far from the carpet weaving centers, tribal rugs bring a feeling of ingenuity and nature, these generations-old techniques and designs, uninfluenced by the market demand or influx of modernity.</div>',0,0),(55,55,'pa_color','',0,2),(59,59,'product_cat','<h2>Shag Rugs And Kilim Ottomans.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">Their long, shaggy fibers and deep pile is what gives a shag carpet that long, plushy feel under your feet. A cultural relic iconic of the 1960s and 70s, shag rugs have resurged in popularity in recent years and transformed to encompass and blend today’s styles, as well as retain the retro feel of the Swinging’ Sixties and Disco Era.</div>',0,0),(60,60,'product_cat','<h3>Animal Prints / Cowhides Rugs</h3>\r\n<div class=\"block-heading-text\">Sustainably sourced from both India and the South American pampas, each one-of-a-kind cowhide rug has a lustrous sheen, contrasting spots, and a broad range of background hues that come alive in natural daylight.</div>',0,0),(61,61,'product_cat','Tapestries are woven on a vertical loom, often feature complex, pictorial designs equivalent in comparison to paintings, and visible from both front and back.',0,0),(62,62,'pa_color','',0,21),(63,63,'pa_color','',0,1),(65,65,'pa_color','',0,2),(66,66,'pa_color','',0,4),(67,67,'pa_color','',0,1),(69,69,'pa_color','',0,2),(71,71,'pa_co